<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="317" pageId="1" pageNumber="316" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1983,2010]" box="[151,1437,1983,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1983,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="316">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Puparia minute; with or without any wax secretion, colourless; wider at first abdominal segment and nar-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,153,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="317">rowed anteriorly and posteriorly; median length of cephalothorax longer than abdomen; margin weakly crenulate; tracheal pore openings differentiated from margin, cleft-like; dorsum faintly tessellated or devoid of tessellations; submargin not differentiated dorsally, distinct on the ventral surface; dorsum lacks granulations; tubercles present; submarginal papillae may be present, usually at anterior and posterior margins only; transverse moulting suture extends posteriorly to the subdorsum and then bends upwards and meets the margin slightly below the thoracic tracheal pore region; thoracic tracheal furrows wanting while caudal tracheal furrow distinct. Vasiform orifice subcordate; operculum subcordate; lingula obscured or exposed. Ventral submargin demarcated by a submarginal ventral fold; thoracic tracheal folds faintly indicated; caudal tracheal fold present.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
